 are more likely to be deleted. -->\nNote: The following list is not exhaustive. Also, it mixes game engines with rendering engines as well as API bindings without any distinctions.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align: center; font-size: 85%; width: auto; table-layout: fixed;\"\n|-\n! style=\"width: 12em\" | Name\n! Primary [[programming language]]\n! [[Scripting language|Scripting]]\n! [[Cross-platform]]\n! 2D/3D oriented\n! Target [[Computing platform|platform]]\n! Notable games\n! License\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes and references\n|-\n! [[4A Engine]]\n| [[C++]]\n| \n| {{Yes}}\n| 3D\n| [[Microsoft Windows|Windows]], [[OS X]], [[Linux]], [[PlayStation 3]], [[PlayStation 4]], [[Xbox 360]], [[Xbox One]]\n| ''[[Metro 2033 (video game)|Metro 2033]]'', ''[[Metro: Last Light]]'', ''[[Metro Exodus]] \n| {{proprietary}}\n|\n|- \n! [[A-Frame (VR)]]\n|HTML, JavaScript\n| JavaScript\n| {{Yes}}\n| 3D\n| [[Cross-platform]]\n| A-Painter<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://blog.mozvr.com/a-painter|title=A-Painter: Paint in VR in Your Browser|date=September 19, 2016|newspaper=Mozilla VR Blog|access-date=October 27, 2016}}</ref>\n| {{free|[[MIT License|MIT]]}}\n| Open source [[Entity component system]] [[WebVR]] framework\n|-\n! [[Adventure Game Interpreter]]\n| \n| C style\n| {{Yes}}\n| 2D\n| [[DOS]], [[Apple SOS]], [[ProDOS]], [[Classic Mac OS]], [[Atari TOS]]\n| [[Adventure Game Interpreter#AGI-based games published by Sierra On-Line|List]]\n| {{proprietary}}\n| \n|-\n! [[Adventure Game Studio]]\n| [[C++]]\n| AGSScript\n| {{Yes}}\n| 2D\n| [[Microsoft Windows|Windows]], [[Linux]]\n| ''[[Chzo Mythos]]'', ''[[Blackwell (series)|Blackwell]]''\n| {{free|[[Artistic License|Artistic]] 2.0}}\n| Mostly used to develop third-person [[Pre-rendering|pre-rendered]] [[Adventure game#Graphic adventure|graphic adventure games]], one of the most popular for developing amateur [[adventure game]]s\n|-\n! [[Petroglyph Games#Alamo Game Engine|Alamo]]\n| \n| \n| {{Yes}}\n| 3D\n| [[Microsoft Windows|Windows]], [[OS X]], [[Xbox 360]]\n| ''[[Star Wars: Empire at War]]'', ''[[Star Wars: Empire at War: Forces of Corruption]]'', ''[[Universe at War: Earth Assault]]''\n| {{proprietary}}\n| \n|-\n! [[Aleph One (game engine)|Aleph One]]\n| [[C++]]\n| [[Lua (programming language)|Lua]], [[Marathon (video game)|Marathon]] markup language\n| {{yes}}\n| 2.5D\n| [[Microsoft Windows|Windows]], [[Linux]], [[OS X]]\n|Aleph One (''[[Marathon (video game)|Marathon]]'' [[Remake (software)|remake]])\n| {{free|[[GNU General Public License|GPL]]}}\n| FPS engine\n|-\n! [[Antiryad Gx]]\n| C, Assembler\n| C, C++, Gel\n| {{Yes}}\n| 2D, 3D\n| [[Microsoft Windows|Windows]], [[DOS]], [[Mac OS]], [[Linux]], [[iOS]], [[Android (operating system)|Android]], [[AmigaOS]], [[AROS]], [[MorphOS]], [[Google Native Client|NACL]]\n| \n| {{proprietary}}\n|\n|-\n! [[Frogatto & Friends|Anura]]\n| C++, FFL<ref name=FFL>{{cite web | url = https://github.com/frogatto/frogatto/wiki/A-Gentle-Introduction-to-Frogatto-Formula-Language | title = A Gentle Introduction to Frogatto Formula Language | publisher = frogatto.com | date = | accessdate = February 14, 2018}}</ref>\n| FFL<ref name=FFL />\n| {{Yes}}\n| 2D\n| [[Microsoft Windows|Windows]], [[Linux]], [[OS X]], [[iOS]], [[Android (operating system)|Android]], [[BlackBerry 10]]\n| [[Frogatto & Friends]], Argentum Age<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.argentumage.com | title = Argentum Age | publisher = argentumage.com | date = | accessdate = February 14, 2018}}</ref>, Cube Trains<ref>{{cite web | url = https://ddr0.github.io/cube%20trains/index.html | title = Cube Trains | publisher = David Roberts | date = | accessdate = February 14, 2018}}</ref>\n| {{free|[[zlib License|zlib]]}}\n| {{citation needed|date=July 2015}}, feature freeze\n|-\n! [[Anvil (game engine)|Anvil]]\n| C++, C#\n| \n| {{Yes}}\n| 3D\n| [[Microsoft Windows|Windows]], [[PlayStation 3]], [[PlayStation 4]], [[PlayStation Vita]], [[Wii U]], [[Xbox 360]], [[Xbox One]]\n| [[Anvil (game engine)#Games using Anvil|List]]\n| {{proprietary}}\n|\n|-\n! [[AppGameKit]]\n| C++, BASIC\n| C#, C++, AGK BASIC\n| {{Yes}}\n| 2D, 3D\n| Windows, Mac, iOS, Android, HTML5, Raspberry Pi\n| Echoes, Driving Test Success Apps, Squashies\n| {{proprietary}}\n|\n|-\n! [[Ardor3D]]\n| Java\n|\n| {{Yes}}\n| 3D\n| [[Cross-platform]]\n|\n| {{free|[[zlib License|zlib]]}}\n| Fork of [[jMonkeyEngine]] 2.0\n|-\n! [[Aurora toolset]]\n| C++\n| [[NWScript]]\n| {{Yes}}\n| 3D\n| [[Microsoft Windows|Windows]], [[Linux]], [[OS X]]\n| ''[[Neverwinter Nights]]''\n| {{proprietary}}\n| \n|-\n! [[BigWorld]]\n| \n| Python\n| {{Yes}}\n| 3D\n| [[Microsoft Windows|Windows]], [[Linux]], [[Xbox 360]], [[PlayStation 3]]\n| [[BigWorld#List of games made with BigWorld technology|List]]\n| {{proprietary}}\n| <!-- Might not be notable, article is for company -->\n|-\n! [[Blend4Web]]\n| [[JavaScript]], [[Python (programming language)|Python]], [[C (programming language)|C]], [[C++]]\n| [[JavaScript]]\n| {{Yes}}\n| 3D\n| [[WebGL]], [[Microsoft Windows|Windows]], [[Linux]], [[OS X]], [[iOS]], [[Android (operating system)|Android]]\n| ''[[Experience Curiosity]]'', ''Petigor's Tale'', ''Back to the Middle Ages''\n| {{some|[[GPLv3]] or [[commercial software|commercial]]}}\n| Game content, including graphics, animation, sound, and physics, is authored in the 3D modeling and animation suite [[Blender (software)|Blender]]<ref name=\"blend4web_about\">{{cite web|url=https://www.blend4web.com/en/ | title=Blend4Web Official Site |publisher=Blend4Web.com |date= |accessdate=June 22, 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n! [[Game Blender|Blender]]\n| C, C++\n| Python\n| {{Yes}}\n| 2D, 3D\n| [[Microsoft Windows|Windows]], [[Linux]], [[OS X]], [[Solaris (operating system)|Solaris]]\n| ''[[Yo Frankie!]]'', ''[[Sintel The Game]]'', ''ColorCube''\n| {{free|[[GNU General Public License|GPL]]}}\n| 2D/3D game engine packaged in a 3D modeler with integrated Bullet physics library<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.blender.org/development/coding-guid